}}'''今日緬甸'''（Myanmar Now）是一家总部位於[[缅甸|缅甸]]的新闻机构，由{{link-en|汤森路透基金会|Thomson Reuters Foundation}}創辦於2015年<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Myanmar Now|url=http://www.trust.org/media-development/programmes/?sfid=a153z00001Bidr1AAB&areaOfFocus=Economic%20and%20Social%20Development|accessdate=2021-02-05|author=Foundation|date=|first=Thomson Reuters|work=Thomson Reuters Foundation|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210214193704/https://www.trust.org/media-development/programmes/?sfid=a153z00001Bidr1AAB&areaOfFocus=Economic%20and%20Social%20Development|archivedate=2021-02-14}}</ref>。該新聞機構發表免費的[[缅甸语|缅甸语]]和[[英语|英语]]新聞報道<ref name=":0" />。该新闻機構自成立以来，有數名记者屢次遭到緬甸军方和司法機關的威胁和攻击<ref>{{Cite web|title=Myanmar Now Reporters Threatened With Arrest by Military|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-now-reporters-threatened-arrest-military.html|accessdate=2021-02-05|date=2018-06-25|work=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210618033256/https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-now-reporters-threatened-arrest-military.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Myanmar Now Journalist Assaulted|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-now-journalist-assaulted.html|accessdate=2021-02-05|date=2017-03-15|work=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210222175454/https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-now-journalist-assaulted.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Investigation into shooting attack on Myanmar journalist goes nowhere {{!}} Reporters without borders|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/investigation-shooting-attack-myanmar-journalist-goes-nowhere|accessdate=2021-02-05|date=2020-12-02|work=RSF|language=en|archive-date=2021-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428155138/https://rsf.org/en/news/investigation-shooting-attack-myanmar-journalist-goes-nowhere}}</ref>。截至2019年9月，今日緬甸共有30名记者<ref>{{Cite web|title='Truth, justice, love': Ko Swe Win on journalism in times of repression|url=https://www.rappler.com/world/asia-pacific/profile-ramon-magsaysay-awardee-2019-ko-swe-win-myanmar|accessdate=2021-02-05|work=Rappler|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213044952/https://www.rappler.com/world/asia-pacific/profile-ramon-magsaysay-awardee-2019-ko-swe-win-myanmar}}</ref>，读者人数超过35万<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Myanmar Now Editor-in-Chief Awarded Asia’s Highest Honor|url=https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-now-founder-ko-swe-win-awarded-asias-highest-honor.html|accessdate=2021-02-05|date=2019-08-02|work=The Irrawaddy|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210222021122/https://www.irrawaddy.com/news/burma/myanmar-now-founder-ko-swe-win-awarded-asias-highest-honor.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=|first=|date=30 August 2019|title=Myanmar journalist Swe Win one of the winners of the Ramon Magsaysay Award|work={{link-en|Mizzima}}|url=http://mizzima.com/article/myanmar-journalist-swe-win-one-winners-ramon-magsaysay-award|accessdate=|archive-date=2021-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320010735/https://www.mizzima.com/article/myanmar-journalist-swe-win-one-winners-ramon-magsaysay-award}}</ref>。

